gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 131, Jazz 128
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Jazz, 131-128. Kevin Durant recorded 38 points, nine rebounds, and nine assists for the Suns, while Devin Booker added 24 points and a new career high 15 assists in the victory. Jordan Clarkson tallied 37 points (5-10 3PM), five assists, and three rebounds for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 1-1 in West Group A play, and 6-6 in the regular season, while the Jazz fall to 2-1 in West Group A play, and 4-8 in the regular season.
